<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">We have chosen a variety of countries that will best
represent the cultural diversity of the students in our school. The countries
have been assigned to houses as follows:<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Normans – Italy<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Romans – Japan<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Saxons – Iran<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">Vikings – Columbia <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">We welcome parental support in helping the children to
prepare for the event at home and as an additional task we encourage the
children to try their hand at making some traditional dishes from these
countries, in order to share with the other students on our celebration day on
Friday 28<sup>th</sup> October.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>

